The paper discusses the combination of informetric analysis and information retrieval, which is primarily used in the field of information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper specifically uses the iSearch test collection, which is derived from the open access arXiv.org preprint server, indicating a connection to the digital libraries sub-category (cs.DL). The study focuses on the physics domain, suggesting a potential connection to the sub-categories of scientific computing (cs.SI) and computational physics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses bibliographic coupling and author-co-citation analysis, which are commonly used in the field of digital libraries and information retrieval (cs.DL).
